# M2 — Streaming (SSE) on the OpenAI path

**Date:** 2026-06-30
**Sprint label:** NEW
**Default labels:** enhancement, backend
**Status:** drafted

Milestone M2: make the OpenAI path stream. Consume the upstream's
`/chat/completions` SSE deltas and re-emit them as a correct Anthropic Messages
event stream (message_start → content_block_* → message_delta → message_stop),
so `CCPROXY_PROFILE=openai claude -p` shows tokens live instead of one buffered
reply. Text-only streaming this milestone; streamed tool calls are part of M3.
Depends on M1 (translation core) and M0 (the anthropic profile keeps its raw SSE
passthrough). The Anthropic streaming protocol is specific, so the emitter and
the upstream parser are built and tested as decoupled pieces first.

